<section xml:id="sec_polyrings_hints">
  <title>Hints for
  <q>Polynomial Rings</q>
  exercises</title>
  <p>
    <xref ref="exercise_poly_poly4">Exercise</xref>(d): Note <m>4=3+1</m> and <m>11=3^2+2</m>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <xref ref="exercise_poly_multform">Exercise</xref>(d): Are there any common factors you can take outside the summations before multiplying?
  </p>
  <p>
    <xref ref="exercise_poly_5Z">Exercise</xref>: Note that if <m>a_2</m> is in <m>5\mathbb{Z}</m>,
    then <m>a_2 = 5a_2^{\prime}</m> where <m>a_2^{\prime}</m> is also an integer.
    The same thing holds for al the other coefficients in <m>p(x)</m> and <m>q(x)</m>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <xref ref="exercise_poly_roots">Exercise</xref>(b): Use the method in <xref ref="rootsingeneral">Section</xref>.
  </p>
</section>